Hey this file is intially created in Git Branch-1,
So now its only visible in Branch-1, it wont be visible in "main"

Adding files and pushing to Branch_1:
git checkout Branch_1 (change the current working Branch from main to Branch_1)
(add the "Branch_1 file" and add content to it)
git add .
git commit -m "file created in Branch_1
git push origin Branch_1 (to reflect in the remote repo)

REMOTE REPOSITORY (GitHub)
origin
│
├── origin/main (All existing files ONLY)
│
└── origin/Branch-1  (All existing files + Branch_1 file is visible as it is created here)

--- NOW this file present in Branch_1 is going to be merged to main branch
DONE


--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Merging Branch_1 with main:

git checkout main (switching to main for merging main and Branch_1)
git diff Branch_1 (compares the Branch_1 with main and shows the modifications)
git merge Branch_1

"Branch_1 file" added from Branch_1 to main succesfully. 


